==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Spectacular
<hw>Spec*tac"u*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Of
or pertaining to a shows; of the nature of a show.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Spectacular</xex> sports.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>G.
Hickes.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Adapted to excite wonder and admiration by a display
of pomp or of scenic effects; <as>as, a <ex>spectacular</ex> celebration
of some event; a <ex>spectacular</ex> play.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Pertaining to spectacles, or glasses for the
eyes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- 4. Unusual and striking. -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spectant</ent>⟦br⟧
